We are well travelled, and aware of the dangers of pickpockets in Rome etc, but never expected to be robbed in a secure environment.	Our safe didn't work and in Italy you must protect your money and your passport.	Oh well, the in-room safe worked and I never, ever felt uncomfortable.	I felt very safe in this area of Rome both during the day and at night.	We locked our wallet and personal papers in the locked safe.	As this was my fourth time in Rome, I can say with some authority that the Cicerone is well-situated in a safe area - within walking distance of many Rome attractions, including the Vatican.